Class PackagedProduct

All Implemented Interfaces:
ProductInfo
public class PackagedProduct
extends java.lang.Object
implements ProductInfo

A PackedProduct represents a single UPC-code-bearing product in the store. Packaged products are sold as discrete single units, and never by weight. Note the difference between 'items' and 'products': A 'product' is a type of good sold at the store, whereas an 'item' is a particular box of that product.
